This paper discusses the performance of TCP over ATM-UBR switches, which are commonly used in network communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses congestion control and buffer management, which are related to communication protocols and algorithms, making cs.COMM (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) another likely category. The paper proposes enhancements to UBR for intelligent drop, which involves designing algorithms and policies, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) possible categories. Finally, the paper discusses the Fair Buffer Allocation scheme, which involves resource allocation and optimization, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category as well.
